column1: Blue = Do not change; Green = free text

column2: Library specified as a list of 20 single parts
All-in-one specification of a transformed construct

column3: Blue text column headers are optional
Click on column headers for more information as to what to put into the column

column1: Short and human friendly name for the part, e.g., "GFP Reporter"
column2: Comments about design decisions. E.g. GC content or restriction sites removed
column3: A description of how the part is meant to function and any information about the part that is not to do with how it was designed.
column4: True if this is a final product to be produced, false if this is an intermediate stage being specified for compactness
column5: If the composite is being placed into a plasmid, provide the name of the plasmid. If the composite is being transformed into the genome, provide the name of the locus for incorporation.
column6: Identity and strand constraints on parts, expressed as Part X RELATION Part Y, where RELATION is "same as", "different from", "same orientation as", "different orientation from"
column7: Part names (left to right: 5'->3') should match the names of other basic or composite parts. Add more columns as needed. Indicate alternatives with commas, RC(name) for reverse complement
